external_knowledge:
Thresholds are used to define the normal operating range of a metric; 
A warning threshold is the value above which a metric is considered to be approaching a critical state but is still within an acceptable range, while a critical threshold is the value above which the metric is considered to be in a critical state; 
These thresholds are used for monitoring and alerting purposes.

